race.comment: TARAWI THERESE (1) was well fancied last time and led throughout to score (25.11) at Shepparton in a Grade 4/5 over 450m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can continue the winning form. DASHING SLAY (4) was out of placings last time (30.36) at Angle Park in a OPEN, finishing fourth and beaten 4.5 lengths. Loves this draw, having won three of five starts. Looks a key chance on best figures. KATIE BELL (3) missed the frame last time but just three runs back was a strong Maiden winner (25.53) at Warrnambool over 450m. Can hit the frame this time. SHE'S PRIMED (2) will give backers a sight.
